OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBig firm bosses' pay rose  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25F16% as workers squeezed    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Bosses at Britain's biggest companies  
OL,6, saw their pay rise by almost 16% on    
OL,7, average last year as most workers'     
OL,8, wages were squeezed by rising prices.  
OL,10,FThe High Pay Centre said the median pay
OL,11,Fof a FTSE 100 chief executive was      
OL,12,F#3.91m in 2022, up from #3.38m in 2021.
OL,14,FAnd it said the average earnings of a  
OL,15,FFTSE 100 boss was 118 times more than a
OL,16,Ftypical UK worker on #33,000 a year.   
OL,18,FCritics called the earnings extreme,   
OL,19,Fbut some of the firms argued they were 
OL,20,Fin line with competitors.              
